snippet.textDisplay:
Brilliant track this.
I would say this is one of the best musical composition so far from Coke Studio. Phenomenal job with the stringed instruments especially by Emon Choudhury (he is out of the world here both in style and strings) and the rustic vocal of Aleya Begum ji makes it even more brilliant of a track. However, the more refined and modern vocal felt a bit of place despite being melodious. 
Another aspect which I always felt is that the tracks in general felt very short despite it being over 5 minutes. This track in particular felt could have been longer and could have explored the rustic and raw vocal of Aleya Begum ji even further along with the harmony vocals/chorus.
